1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,160
But you caught Pae.

2
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,400
He's just a lackey.

3
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,720
Thongyoo is still free
and I can't catch him.

4
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,520
Good has to defeat evil.

5
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,600
Bandit Wad.

6
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:17,280
- Hey!
- If Lasor truly killed your father,

7
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:19,440
I'll deal with him myself.

8
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:22,600
Phraya Kaipetch, Governor of Tha Khiri.

9
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:25,280
Dad, you and Master know each other?

10
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,080
You didn't just try to
erase sorcery from your son,

11
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,320
you even tried to wipe Lasor's memories.

12
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,880
I'll protect him with my life.

13
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,400
If you step forward,

14
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,440
don't blame me for being ungrateful.

15
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:38,040
He intends to use Lasor
as a pawn to take revenge on me.

16
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:40,520
But, Yiwha,
I have something I need your help with.

17
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:56,320
Yiwha.

18
00:02:57,240 --> 00:03:00,680
Yes. It's me. Were you trying to kill me?

19
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,360
Where did you disappear to?

20
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:12,280
I went to look for the truth from Dad,

21
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:18,640
but patrol units were everywhere, so I…

22
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,920
came back here.

23
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:28,960
In the end, you couldn't go anywhere.
You still came back to me.

24
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:33,080
So, are you going to trust me now?

25
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Mhm.

26
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,600
I'll listen to everything you say.

27
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,000
Are you sure?

28
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:55,320
Yiam isn't dead, is he?

29
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,440
You knew?

30
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,800
Your eyes give you away.

31
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,320
If something had happened to him,

32
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,200
you wouldn't have come back to me.

33
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:12,480
Yiam survived because of Klaikot Lek Lai.

34
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,440
That's why I need your help.

35
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,880
What do you want me to do?

36
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:22,480
Find a way
to destroy the Lek Lai inside Yiam.

37
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,720
You've seen how it hurts him, right?

38
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,800
How badly it tortures him.

39
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,640
And more importantly,

40
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,800
if the Lek Lai remains inside Yiam,

41
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,600
your brother won't survive either.

42
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,320
Yiwha,

43
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,680
you're the only one

44
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,840
who can get close enough to him.

45
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,000
<i>Lady Duen.</i>

46
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,320
<i>Lady Duen.</i>

47
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,840
Lady Duen.

48
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:48,800
Lady Duen.

49
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,680
Lasor! Lasor!

50
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:56,080
A ghost! A ghost!

51
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:03,640
What ghost? There's nothing here.

52
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,960
Were you dreaming?

53
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,080
I wasn't dreaming. I really saw it.

54
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:13,080
A man's ghost, his face was mangled.
He was standing by my bed.

55
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:37,560
There's nothing here. Go back to sleep.

56
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:41,360
Where are you going?

57
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,680
I'll sleep outside.

58
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:51,120
That way the ghost won't dare bother you.

59
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,080
Sleep here with me.

60
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:06,480
I can't.
If anyone sees us, it wouldn't be proper.

61
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,000
Please, Lasor.

62
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,320
Please. I'm scared.

63
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,280
Stay here with me.

64
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:37,840
There's an order
to suspend transferring Pae

65
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:39,960
for questioning
at the Provincial Patrol Department.

66
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:45,240
The new governor from the capital
will personally decide the case.

67
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,320
PATROL UNIT

68
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,560
How's the new governor? Is he good?

69
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,920
Phraya Kaipetch, a high-ranking noble

70
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:58,000
with strong connections in the capital.
No wife, no children.

71
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,720
Originally from Tani.

72
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,360
I tried digging into his background,

73
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,360
but there's barely any information.

74
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,960
Strange. A powerful noble,

75
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:13,640
yet hardly known. He seems mysterious.

76
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,440
Probably the same kind as Duang.

77
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:21,720
Tha Khiri's full of bandits, no decent man
would be sent here as governor.

78
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:28,320
Pun, have you heard anything about Yiwha?

79
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,920
I don't believe Yiwha killed the governor.

80
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:41,160
But we still need to bring her in
for questioning

81
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,160
to find out
who that masked bandit really is.

82
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,320
Pun!

83
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,800
Pun! We've got a situation!

84
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,480
PATROL SCHEDULE

85
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,040
How did this happen?

86
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:04,040
I think he was under too much stress.
He probably killed himself last night.

87
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,200
We're screwed.

88
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,520
Pae's dead.
Thongyoo and his people walk free.

89
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,560
You did everything you could, Pun.

90
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,680
My informant in the police force reported

91
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:42,760
that Pae committed suicide.

92
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,680
Good. If Pae is dead, that's good.

93
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:50,040
That's one less enemy for me.

94
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:55,760
The land along the railway route,

95
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:58,360
I plan to build pleasure houses,

96
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:02,920
casinos, brothels,
liquor dens, opium houses,

97
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,960
to carry on Phraya Decha's legacy.

98
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:08,280
What do you think, Tim?

99
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,520
An excellent idea, sir.

100
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:14,680
Our city will become a major
trading port of the southern provinces.

101
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:18,400
The people will prosper,
and Tha Khiri will flourish

102
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:21,600
thanks to your prestige.

103
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,560
You're good at flattery.

104
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:27,800
No wonder

105
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:30,320
you've survived

106
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,520
through so many governors.

107
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:37,720
But I prefer people who flatter me
with results, not words.

108
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,160
Ah.

109
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,520
Yes, sir.

110
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,000
Lasor.

111
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,120
Yes, sir.

112
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:50,320
I will appoint you as head
of the railway construction unit,

113
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:52,960
replacing Tim.

114
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:56,880
Of course, sir.

115
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,280
Tim, do you have a problem with that?

116
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,920
No, sir. It's entirely

117
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,720
up to your judgment.

118
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,720
I will work with full dedication.

119
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,200
I won't disappoint you, Master.

120
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:18,880
Very good.

121
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,000
The sooner the railway is completed,

122
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:26,040
the more people will indulge in vice.

123
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,880
And it'll be easier for me to rule.

124
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,000
Isn't that right?

125
00:12:56,360 --> 00:13:00,280
But I don't know sorcery. How can I
destroy the Lek Lai inside Yiam, Dad?

126
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,760
A woman's menstrual blood.

127
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:12,120
A woman's menstrual blood carries a curse.
No matter how powerful the sorcery may be,

128
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,160
if it touches menstrual blood,

129
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,320
it will deteriorate.

130
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,400
Klaikot Lek Lai is no exception.

131
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:32,760
Yiam!

132
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,960
What is it?

133
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,680
No.

134
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:37,200
It's nothing.

135
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,520
Then why are you hiding it?

136
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:59,480
Oh, I thought it was something else.

137
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:02,160
There's nothing to be embarrassed about.

138
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,600
We're husband and wife already, Yiwha.

139
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,200
What are you going to do next?

140
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:19,520
I have to find the one who killed Duang.

141
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:24,280
If we didn't kill him, why are we running?

142
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:28,640
Wouldn't turning ourselves in be better,
to prove our innocence

143
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:30,720
and help catch the real culprit?

144
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,760
I'm afraid the police
might be working for them.

145
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:46,120
I know a policeman at Huai Yao station.
His name is Pun.

146
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:47,920
You know him too?

147
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,360
Pun is my friend.

148
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,520
He'll help us.

149
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,280
But Tim's men are hunting us down.

150
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,600
How are we supposed to get to Pun?

151
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,720
I have a plan.

152
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,280
- Hey.
- Hey.

153
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,640
- Go.
- Go.

154
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,680
MASKED MAN, YIWHA

155
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,920
- Go.
- Go.

156
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,080
Hey, wait.

157
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,280
Where are you going?

158
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
We're going to see a doctor
in the city for leprosy.

159
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,080
Yikes!

160
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,440
Just go already.
I don't want your disease infecting me.

161
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:29,520
Go!

162
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:56,000
With just the Narai Transformation Spell,
they couldn't recognize us at all.

163
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:01,200
If you can disguise yourself as others,
have you ever considered

164
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,280
that the person who killed your family

165
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:07,520
might have been someone using the spell,
posing as my father or Lasor?

166
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:17,280
I'll scout inside. You wait here.

167
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,320
Phraya Kaipetch,

168
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,640
the new governor,

169
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:35,520
plans to build massive pleasure houses
once the railway is done.

170
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,760
From now on, our city
will be flooded with vice,

171
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,160
liquor, and illegal drugs.

172
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,840
What kind of thinking turns
a port city into a sin city?

173
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:48,040
Aren't bandits and thieves
already bad enough?

174
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:51,880
Isn't anyone daring enough to oppose him?

175
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,560
Who would dare?

176
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,480
Everyone fears
Phraya Kaipetch's influence.

177
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,600
They're afraid of getting in trouble.

178
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:04,839
If only Khun Yod and Yiam
were still alive…

179
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,520
Masked bandit!

180
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,200
Stop. Don't move!

181
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:18,760
Yiam!

182
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:22,880
- Yiam!
- Yiam.

183
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:24,680
Yiam.

184
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:32,280
This is Talong, Chin Yuan's son.
You can trust him.

185
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,000
Don't tell me

186
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,440
the mysterious masked bandit was you.

187
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:43,880
I dressed as the masked man because
I didn't want anyone to know I was alive.

188
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,840
Then where have you been all these years?

189
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,680
I'll tell you later.

190
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,760
Come out.

191
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,520
This is Yiwha. She's my wife.

192
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:14,560
Wife?

193
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:34,720
You two can hide at my place for now.

194
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,440
Thank you so much, Talong.

195
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:46,160
You, Pun, and I,

196
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,520
we all share similar fates.

197
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:52,040
Our fathers were brutally murdered,

198
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:55,760
yet none of us ever received
justice from the law.

199
00:18:57,880 --> 00:19:01,360
If we can't rely on anyone else,
then we'll rely on ourselves.

200
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,920
I'll uproot them completely
and wipe them out.

201
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,960
If you and Yiwha didn't kill Duang,
then who did?

202
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:19,760
I suspect he's a master of dark sorcery.

203
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:23,760
He might be connected
to the same people who murdered my family.

204
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,280
Who is it, Yiam?

205
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:05,720
You and I are in the same boat now.

206
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,920
If we don't help each other
find the one who killed Duang,

207
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:14,280
we'll both end up condemned prisoners,
beheaded and displayed.

208
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,920
With Lek Lai inside you,
are you afraid of dying?

209
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,160
I'm not afraid of dying.

210
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:28,120
I'm afraid you might die.

211
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,520
Why?

212
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,400
Everyone who's born eventually dies.

213
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,640
But I'd rather grow old
and die together with you.

214
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,360
Now that Petch has returned,

215
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:57,840
he wants revenge against us.

216
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,080
Could Yod's death have been his doing?

217
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,920
Maybe or maybe not.

218
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:10,200
Everyone who knew the truth is dead.

219
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,640
Only Yiam is left.

220
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,360
Yiam misunderstood.

221
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:19,120
He thinks Lasor and I killed Yod.

222
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:26,160
The day Yod died,
my Chum Suea was destroyed.

223
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:29,520
Everything felt carefully planned,

224
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:33,680
as if it was meant to stop me
from helping Yod in time.

225
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:40,360
That day, the authorities
raided Chum Suea.

226
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:44,720
But Duang is already dead.
Who can we get the truth from now?

227
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:49,800
Duang is dead, but Tim is still alive.

228
00:21:50,760 --> 00:21:54,160
Only Tim can tell us what really happened.

229
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:12,440
Why are you avoiding me?

230
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,160
Talk to me first.

231
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,720
Is there something
you wish me to do, Sir Lasor?

232
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:28,280
The night Phraya Decha was killed,
what really happened?

233
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,720
Tell me.

234
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:37,280
It was the masked bandit and your sister.

235
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,600
Your sister, sir.

236
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:45,640
Yiwha would never kill anyone. Tell me.

237
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,880
Did Phraya Decha have any other enemies?

238
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:53,440
No one would dare oppose him.

239
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:56,120
He had a powerful backer,
a high-ranking noble in the capital.

240
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:08,600
Then the destruction of Chum Suea
was also ordered by Phraya Decha, right?

241
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,200
I…

242
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,320
Argh!

243
00:23:56,560 --> 00:24:00,200
If you think this bastard is so righteous,
don't call yourself my son.

244
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,680
<i>If you don't want me as your son,</i>

245
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:12,800
then I won't be your son anymore.

246
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,560
I'm ready.

247
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,600
Are you sure?

248
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:29,040
Once you decide to become my son,

249
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:32,200
there's no turning back.

250
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:52,920
I've decided.

251
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,640
From this moment on,

252
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:01,240
I will acknowledge only you as my father.

253
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,520
Good.

254
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:32,600
Give me your hand.

255
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:54,080
Repeat after me.

256
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,720
From this moment onward…

257
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:01,120
From this moment onward…

258
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:04,520
if I am false or deceitful,

259
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:08,680
if I betray or deceive,
may I perish in ruin.

260
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:13,320
This is the blood oath
of Bandit Wad's Chum Suea.

261
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:19,120
Are you going to say it or not?

262
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:29,440
If I betray or deceive,

263
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,000
may I perish in ruin,

264
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:36,400
die by spear and blade,
my blood soaking the earth.

265
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:41,120
By the power of vengeful spirits
and damned ghosts,

266
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,880
may all our kin and companions

267
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:45,240
die violent deaths within three days,

268
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:48,360
not lasting three months,
not enduring three years,

269
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:52,640
and fall into Avici Hell
for endless lifetimes.

270
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,480
Why are you here?

271
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,120
Ugh!

272
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:22,040
- Ugh!
- Lady Duen.

273
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,360
Lasor, help me.

274
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,240
You nosy bitch!

275
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,360
My lady.

276
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:37,800
My lady.

277
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:40,400
What did you see just now?

278
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:45,440
I… I didn't see anything.

279
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:49,240
You can lie to anyone, but not me!

280
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,480
My lady,

281
00:28:57,320 --> 00:29:00,200
go back to your room.

282
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:02,080
Go.

283
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:07,680
Lasor.

284
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,840
She knows too much already.

285
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:14,600
You can't let her go.

286
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:18,320
Master,

287
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,240
what do you want me to do?

288
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:30,960
Kill her.

289
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,600
Kill her.

290
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,080
You're awake, my lady?

291
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:09,120
Lasor.

292
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:14,200
Don't kill me. I'm scared.
Please, don't kill me.

293
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,000
No one's going to kill you.

294
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,760
You must have had a nightmare.

295
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,400
But I saw it.

296
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,160
I stayed by your side all night.

297
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:29,640
You slept peacefully.

298
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,320
But…

299
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,760
But I really saw it.

300
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:38,640
I saw you, with Phraya Kaipetch.

301
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,200
Kill her.

302
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:48,560
The wound.

303
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,520
You should have a wound.

304
00:30:56,760 --> 00:30:58,680
My lady.

305
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:00,400
I told you.

306
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,760
It was just a nightmare.

307
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:07,160
Go wash your face. You'll feel better.

308
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:56,680
Master,

309
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:01,000
if you're going to kill her,

310
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,120
then kill me too.

311
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,880
You love her?

312
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:19,400
Yes.

313
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:24,360
Lasor,

314
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:28,880
love is your weakness.

315
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:32,400
It will block your rise to greatness.

316
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:36,000
Remember my words.

317
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:39,040
Whatever you love

318
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:41,560
will be what kills you.

319
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:46,880
One day, you'll regret

320
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,520
not killing this woman.

321
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,920
Tim…

322
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,639
We came too late.

323
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:29,199
The body is completely mangled.
The bones are broken and twisted.

324
00:34:29,719 --> 00:34:31,560
He was killed with dark magic.

325
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,840
Then his body was fed
to the spirits he keeps.

326
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:39,199
Could this be Lasor's doing?

327
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:45,600
Petch also knows dark magic.
It could be him.

328
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:50,239
I must get Lasor away from Kaipetch

329
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:53,600
before everything becomes even worse.

330
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:01,960
The police believe
Tim was killed by a wild animal.

331
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,200
A tiger or a bear.

332
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,280
That's why the body was badly torn apart.

333
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,240
I think it was done by a person.

334
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,280
Who do you think it was?

335
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:19,400
Something feels strange.

336
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,200
The governor ordered
the case closed immediately.

337
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,760
No investigation at all.

338
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,600
Something's definitely wrong.

339
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:32,480
Then what can the police do?

340
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:46,400
When the law can't protect anyone,

341
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:51,160
we'll use our own rules to protect
those who never received justice.

342
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:14,720
Hurry up.

343
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:17,480
If you slow down,

344
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,000
don't expect

345
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:21,920
a single bite of food

346
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:23,680
or a drop of water.

347
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,600
I've been working day and night.

348
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:39,800
Please let me rest a bit, Sir Lasor.

349
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:49,840
Sure.

350
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:52,880
Look at me.

351
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,920
Are you trying to challenge me, old man?

352
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:03,320
I… I wouldn't dare.

353
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:07,560
You really want to rest?

354
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,000
Fine.

355
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:12,960
I'll be generous.

356
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,280
Hey.

357
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:24,120
- Come here.
- Ugh!

358
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:26,600
Come here.

359
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:34,200
Anyone else

360
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,640
want to rest?

361
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:00,520
Once the railway is finished,

362
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:03,600
Phraya Kaipetch
will have both wealth and power.

363
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:07,600
Is what he has already still not enough?

364
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:10,920
Human greed has no end.

365
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:12,880
It's never satisfied.

366
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:17,720
The authorities ordered the railway
construction. Who would dare oppose it?

367
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:20,200
They'd probably be branded as rebels.

368
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:24,240
I heard rebels, if caught,

369
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:29,240
get their skulls smashed open, a red-hot
iron clamped into brains. Is that true?

370
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:31,080
It is.

371
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:32,520
I've seen it with my own eyes.

372
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:36,840
So we're just going to
let them finish the railway?

373
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,640
Never.

374
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:43,080
What are you going to do?

375
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,160
Yiam. Yiam!

376
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:17,560
Hey!

377
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,880
Hey!

378
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:29,760
Let's go.

379
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:32,600
Go.

380
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,000
What is going on?

381
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,120
Master.

382
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:53,880
I know. The railway was bombed.

383
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:55,840
Yes.

384
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:59,240
The workers say it was the masked guy.

385
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:02,240
He's deliberately destroying our railway.

386
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,520
You know who he is?

387
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,720
Yiam.

388
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:17,120
Yiam has declared himself my enemy.

389
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,800
As long as Klaikot Lek Lai

390
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,320
remains in his body,

391
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:30,120
no one can touch him.

392
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:37,280
Master,
is there really no way to defeat him?

393
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:41,920
There is a way.

394
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,800
Aren't you afraid
of being charged with rebellion?

395
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:54,440
If I were afraid, I wouldn't do it.

396
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:59,760
The only thing that lets evil triumph
is good people standing by

397
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:02,120
and submitting to it.

398
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,400
That's why I have to be the masked man.

399
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:06,920
So how long are you going to stay one?

400
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:09,600
I don't know.

401
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,000
Why ask?

402
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:18,960
Afraid I'll be caught as a rebel,
have my skull cracked open

403
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:21,280
and a red-hot iron shoved into my brain?

404
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:26,200
Don't joke about that.
Phraya Kaipetch isn't ordinary.

405
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,120
Whatever you do,

406
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,960
be careful.

407
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:43,240
Yiam's got real guts.

408
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:46,360
I never thought he'd change this much.

409
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:50,200
If I did what Yiam did,

410
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,840
would you praise me too?

411
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:06,920
If I died,

412
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:09,640
would you miss me?

413
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:27,160
Is it that funny?

414
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:38,320
Are you mad at me?

415
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:45,880
If I died,

416
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,360
you'd probably be happy, wouldn't you?

417
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,880
WANTED

418
00:43:11,960 --> 00:43:16,200
Pun, I made some <i>khao tom mud</i>. You and
your friends can eat it during your shift.

419
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:18,160
- Here.
- Thank you.

420
00:43:18,240 --> 00:43:19,640
Lucky day again, guys.

421
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:22,160
- Thanks, Noree.
- Sure.

422
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:29,560
Hey, hey, easy. Leave some for me.

423
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:30,640
This one's yours.

424
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:31,840
Hm.

425
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:35,240
These guys are always fastest
when it comes to food.

426
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:43,280
Have you been busy lately? I haven't
seen you come by the house much.

427
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:44,760
Mm.

428
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:46,520
Cases every single day.

429
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:50,960
Old ones aren't cleared yet,
and new ones keep coming.

430
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:54,600
I barely have time to eat a proper meal.

431
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:55,960
Mm.

432
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:57,960
You must be exhausted.

433
00:43:58,040 --> 00:44:01,240
If there's anything you want to eat,
just tell me. I'll make it for you.

434
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:07,600
Just seeing your face already fills me up.

435
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:35,800
Take your time.

436
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:39,400
Finish eating first. I'm not in a hurry.

437
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,720
Then I'll head back.

438
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:48,400
- Alright.
- Alright.

439
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:14,520
I'm here to file a report.
Someone bombed the governor's railway.

440
00:45:16,800 --> 00:45:19,120
Who did it? Do you know who's responsible?

441
00:45:20,640 --> 00:45:22,240
It's Yiam. Your friend.

442
00:45:23,960 --> 00:45:25,680
The one disguised as the masked man,

443
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:31,040
committing rebellion
and destroying state property.

444
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:36,760
That's impossible. Yiam is dead.

445
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:47,240
Are you sure?

446
00:45:53,560 --> 00:45:55,240
These rebels are dangerous.

447
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:57,840
They operate as an organization.

448
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:01,600
They deserve
to have their skulls cracked open.

449
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:06,720
What about those who sell out the country,
steal from the people,

450
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:11,400
and turn the land into a den of vice?

451
00:46:12,280 --> 00:46:13,600
They're rebels too.

452
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:17,040
I'd like to see

453
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:20,520
whose skull gets cracked open first.

454
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:23,680
Even if they're both rebels,

455
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,880
the one with more power

456
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:29,720
is always innocent.

457
00:46:46,040 --> 00:46:47,080
Yes, sir.

458
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:52,040
- You're one of Khun Paeng's men, right?
- Yes, sir.

459
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:56,560
Good. Keep a close eye
on Pun and his group.

460
00:46:57,200 --> 00:46:58,840
Report to me if anything happens.

461
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:00,760
Yes, Sir Lasor.

462
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:22,280
Phraya Kaipetch plans to build the railway
from Khuan Phra-ngam,

463
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:24,960
through Tha Khiri,
all the way down to Huai Yao.

464
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:26,720
Both sides of the track

465
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:29,520
have already been bought up
by Tycoon Thongyoo.

466
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:33,320
Anyone who refused to sell was killed.

467
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:36,000
Absolutely vile.

468
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,960
Hell must've sent him.

469
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:41,840
We need to blow up this mountain pass.

470
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:46,680
If the railway can't pass through this
into Khuan Phra-ngam,

471
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:49,040
our towns will be safe.

472
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,520
But I can't do this alone.

473
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:54,960
Are you willing
to risk your lives with me?

474
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:58,080
I'm in. Whatever happens, happens.

475
00:47:59,840 --> 00:48:02,000
Me too. Live or die.

476
00:48:08,360 --> 00:48:09,320
Yiam,

477
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:12,000
I want you to think carefully.

478
00:48:14,640 --> 00:48:18,440
What's with you, Pun? We're already
this far. What's left to think about?

479
00:48:19,280 --> 00:48:21,640
Earlier today,
Lasor came to see me at the station.

480
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:26,320
He already knows you're alive
and that you're the masked man.

481
00:48:29,720 --> 00:48:32,640
Yiam, you'll be charged as a rebel.

482
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:35,120
That's execution for seven generations.

483
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:43,160
My dad, my mom,

484
00:48:43,240 --> 00:48:45,640
my sister, they're all dead.

485
00:48:46,400 --> 00:48:48,200
I've got nothing left to lose, Pun.

486
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:52,600
Even if it costs me my life,
I have to stop them

487
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:55,360
If I bring them down,

488
00:48:55,960 --> 00:48:59,520
the land will finally be at peace.
Isn't that a good thing?

489
00:49:12,560 --> 00:49:13,800
It's too dangerous.

490
00:49:14,760 --> 00:49:15,760
I'm not going.

491
00:49:43,960 --> 00:49:47,840
Right now, my family
must be among the stars.

492
00:49:51,600 --> 00:49:55,520
Nui and everyone from Chum Suea
who has passed away must be there too.

493
00:49:57,320 --> 00:50:00,040
They must all be happy now.

494
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,840
How do you know they're happy?

495
00:50:09,880 --> 00:50:11,520
I don't really know.

496
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:15,960
I just want to believe in
whatever brings me peace.

497
00:50:24,760 --> 00:50:25,840
Yiam,

498
00:50:27,200 --> 00:50:30,400
what are you going to do next
about the railway construction?

499
00:50:39,840 --> 00:50:41,160
If we want to stop this,

500
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:46,440
we have to cut off
the governor's arms and legs first.

501
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:50,080
That means I have to stop Lasor.

502
00:50:56,600 --> 00:50:58,560
I'll go talk to Lasor myself.

503
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:02,520
Are you sure you can stop your brother?

504
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:09,880
Right now he's intoxicated by power,
status, and wealth.

505
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:26,840
Don't worry.

506
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:31,320
I won't use Lek Lai to harm your brother

507
00:51:33,800 --> 00:51:36,240
if he stops doing evil,

508
00:51:36,320 --> 00:51:40,360
turns himself in,
and confesses everything.

509
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:58,680
I'll go in and confront Lasor.
You two wait here.

510
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:01,840
Let us go with you.
If something happens, we can help.

511
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:05,600
That's right. Petch is cunning.

512
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:07,960
He won't let you meet Lasor easily.

513
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:13,800
Lasor is stubborn. He listens to no one.
Only I can stop him.

514
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:17,440
How will we know you're still safe?

515
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:20,680
I'll only be inside
for as long as one incense stick burns.

516
00:52:20,760 --> 00:52:24,160
If I don't come back,
it means I've fallen into his trap.

517
00:52:28,680 --> 00:52:29,880
Be careful.

518
00:52:51,840 --> 00:52:52,880
Lasor.

519
00:53:10,240 --> 00:53:11,280
Lasor.

520
00:53:18,760 --> 00:53:19,960
Why did you follow me, Dad?

521
00:53:21,960 --> 00:53:24,640
You can't stay here. Come back with me.

522
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:28,120
Why can't I? This is my home.

523
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:32,040
Petch wants to use you
to take revenge on me.

524
00:53:32,560 --> 00:53:34,040
You're being used as a pawn.

525
00:53:36,320 --> 00:53:37,360
Lasor,

526
00:53:38,720 --> 00:53:40,040
come back with me, my son.

527
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:49,400
"Come back with me, my son."

528
00:53:50,840 --> 00:53:52,040
Wad,

529
00:53:52,640 --> 00:53:56,000
you only realized that now?
Isn't it a little too late?

530
00:53:57,040 --> 00:53:58,120
Petch,

531
00:53:58,640 --> 00:54:01,640
if you want revenge, fight me.

532
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:03,600
Don't drag my son into this.

533
00:54:04,520 --> 00:54:05,960
Hey.

534
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:09,480
I didn't drag your son into anything.
Your son came to me himself.

535
00:54:10,960 --> 00:54:12,160
And besides,

536
00:54:13,600 --> 00:54:15,400
I don't want to fight with you.

537
00:54:16,480 --> 00:54:19,240
I prefer a sneak attack.

538
00:55:05,960 --> 00:55:08,000
<i>Ka sa ca pha…</i>

539
00:55:08,840 --> 00:55:11,240
Don't waste your strength, Wad.

540
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:13,840
I've sealed this place completely.

541
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:16,640
Petch, you bastard.

542
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:18,680
I'll kill you no matter what.

543
00:55:19,720 --> 00:55:21,520
You? Kill me?

544
00:55:24,280 --> 00:55:26,560
Wait until I capture Chaem and Niem first.

545
00:55:26,640 --> 00:55:31,640
Then I'll send all three of you
to join Yod in hell.

546
00:55:31,720 --> 00:55:32,600
Petch!

547
00:55:48,080 --> 00:55:50,480
Wad's been inside a long time.
Why hasn't he come out yet?

548
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:55,880
Something bad must have happened.

549
00:55:57,760 --> 00:55:59,040
Let's go in and help him.

550
00:55:59,840 --> 00:56:00,680
What?

551
00:56:02,080 --> 00:56:03,080
Look.

552
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:16,400
If you're scared, don't go. I'll go alone.

553
00:56:16,480 --> 00:56:18,320
- Hey, wait.
- What now?

554
00:56:20,760 --> 00:56:22,480
I think Petch knows.

555
00:56:23,240 --> 00:56:24,600
We'll die for nothing.

556
00:56:27,720 --> 00:56:29,040
Let's pull back and regroup.

557
00:56:43,520 --> 00:56:44,840
I have to eat human flesh?

558
00:56:44,920 --> 00:56:47,720
Fresh flesh from Old Master Khrua Phut

559
00:56:47,800 --> 00:56:52,960
<i>is more powerful than any sacred item</i>
<i>in the world. Nothing can resist it.</i>

560
00:56:53,040 --> 00:56:56,400
Not even Yiam's Klaikot Lek Lai.

561
00:56:57,440 --> 00:56:59,920
<i>I saw someone standing</i>
<i>on the water, staring at me,</i>

562
00:57:00,440 --> 00:57:02,760
<i>before transforming</i>
<i>into a black crow and flying away.</i>

563
00:57:02,840 --> 00:57:05,040
It might be the one
who tore out Duang's heart.

564
00:57:05,120 --> 00:57:07,520
We need to show them
what happens to rebels.

565
00:57:07,600 --> 00:57:10,600
<i>Everyone around me</i>
<i>is now hanging by a thread.</i>

566
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:12,880
<i>Phraya Kaipetch won't let anyone go.</i>

567
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:21,320
Just as all clay vessels made
by a potter are destined to break,

568
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,600
- so is life--
- Save your sermon for the next life.

569
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:10,960
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
